AGI - A 26-year-old skier died this morning on the Ortles in South Tyrol after falling while hiking with another person. The tragedy was consumed at about 3,700 meters along the steep 'Minnigerode' canal that descends from the summit at 3,905 meters.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The victim is a Dutch citizen with an Italian passport. According to the first information of the rescuers, the man had reached the peak of the mountain at 9 o'clock and together with the companion of the excursion had begun the descent along the south side. Probably because of the fog, the skilpinist fell and then crashed for about 500 meters. The alarm was launched by another group.&nbsp; rescuers arrived from Solda also with the elixosphere 'Pelikan 3' but the hiker had already died. The body was transported to the nearby hospital of Silandro.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Tom Arent Van de Plassche is the 26-year-old skier who died today after falling along the difficult 'Minigerode' road on the Ortles in South Tyrol. Tom was born in Holland but has been resident in Trentino for years where he worked for a mountain clothing company as well as being an athlete of the runner and engaged in environmental protection.&nbsp;

